The National Executive Committee (NEC) meeting of the African National Congress (ANC) will take place on Wednesday. The first virtual NEC meeting for the year 2021 will deliberate on the up-coming January 8th Statement to be delivered by the party president, Cyril Ramaphosa. In a statement, the ANC says this NEC meeting will discuss among other things, the theme for the ANC’s 109th birthday celebrations. The party confirmed that these celebrations will also be conducted virtually this coming Friday. This year’s celebration will honour the second president of the party, Sefako Makgatho. Makgatho was ANC president between 1917 and 1924. The provinces will be connected virtually to curb the spread of the COVID-19 pandemic. The celebrations will be held at Seleteng in Ga-Mphahlele, where Makgatho was born. ANC briefing on 109th birthday celebrations: